                  <h3 style="font-weight:bold; display:inline;"><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>SEC. 36.</i></font></h3> <font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>Item 2245-401 is added to Section 2.00 of the Budget Act of 2026, to read:</i></font>
               </div><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i></i></font>
               <div><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>
                  <table frame="">
                     <tr>
                        <td colspan="8" valign="top" width="416">
                           <div style="">2245-401—Of the amount appropriated for the implementation of the Disaster Rebuilding Assistance Program, any expenditures pursuant
                              to paragraph (4) of subdivision (b) of Section 51349.4 of the Health and Safety Code that exceed the threshold set forth in
                              subparagraph (B) of that paragraph are authorized only upon the occurrence of both of the following
                           </div>
                        </td>
                     </tr>
                     <tr>
                        <td valign="top" width="24"></td>
                        <td valign="top" width="24">1.</td>
                        <td colspan="5" valign="top" width="288">Approval of an expenditure plan by the Department of Finance.</td>
                        <td align="right" valign="bottom" width="80"></td>
                     </tr>
                     <tr>
                        <td valign="top" width="24"></td>
                        <td valign="top" width="24">2.</td>
                        <td colspan="5" valign="top" width="288">Any expenditures shall be authorized not sooner than 30 days
                           					 after notification in writing of the Department of Finance’s approval of an expenditure plan to the chairpersons of
                           the committees in each house of the Legislature that consider the state budget, the chairpersons of the committees and appropriate
                           subcommittees in each house of the Legislature that consider appropriations, and the Chairperson of the Joint Legislative
                           Budget Committee, or not sooner than whatever lesser time after that notification the chairperson of the joint committee,
                           or the chairperson’s designee, may determine.
                        </td>
                        <td align="right" valign="bottom" width="80"></td>
                     </tr>
                  </table></i></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i></i></font>
               </div>
            </div>
